com.coveros.selenified.element.check

Interface Equals

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AssertEquals, VerifyEquals, WaitForEquals

    public interface Equals
    Equals extends Check to provide some additional checking capabilities. It will handle all checks performed on the actual element. These asserts are custom to the framework, and in addition to providing easy object oriented capabilities, they take screenshots with each check to provide additional traceability, and assist in troubleshooting and debugging failing tests. Equals checks that elements have a particular value associated to them.
    Version:
    3.2.0
    Author:
    Max Saperstone

        Parameters:
        expectedMatches - the expected number of elements matching the locator

      • checkMatches

        default int checkMatches(int expectedMatches,
                         double waitFor,
                         double timeTook)
        Checks that the element has a the expected number of matches on the page, e.g. how many elements match the locator and target provided. If the element isn't present, or the css doesn't contain the desired attribute, this will constitute a failure, same as a mismatch. This information will be logged and recorded, with a screenshot for traceability and added debugging support.
        Parameters:
        expectedMatches - the expected number of elements matching the locator
        waitFor - - if waiting, how long to wait for (set to 0 if no wait is desired)
        timeTook - - the amount of time it took for wait for something (assuming we had to wait)
        Returns:
        Integer: the number of elements matching the locator

      • elementPresent

        default double elementPresent(double seconds)
        Performs a simple check for the element to be present. The provided wait time will be used and the total time the action took will be returned. Nohing will be logged, but this will be used as part of other methods.

        Returns:
